{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:27:14.591780+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Both write methods returned 403 errors (permission denied by the access token). This is a permissions limitation I cannot resolve by retrying.\n\n---\n\nHere's my complete analysis and the exact changes needed for **Issue #6**:\n\n## Issue #6 Analysis: \"Update the safe scan profile\"\n\n### What's requested\nAdjust the safe local scan profile to **include service/version detection** while keeping scope restricted to localhost, updating both `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml` and `scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`.\n\n### Current state\nBoth files already use `-sV` (service/version detection), but the profile YAML doesn't **explicitly document** this as a feature of the profile, and the script doesn't have a descriptive comment explaining its purpose.\n\n### Changes needed\n\n**1. `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** — Add a `features` section to explicitly declare service/version detection:\n\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\nfeatures:\n  - service_version_detection\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**2. `scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** — Add a header comment documenting that this performs service/version detection:\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n# Safe local scan: service/version detection (-sV), localhost only\nTARGET=${1:-127.0.0.1}\ncase \"$TARGET\" in\n  127.0.0.1|localhost) ;;\n  *) echo \"Refusing to scan non-local target: $TARGET\" >&2; exit 2 ;;\nesac\nnmap -sV --top-ports 100 -oX reports/local_scan.xml \"$TARGET\"\n```\n\n### Validation\nThe repo's validation script (`validate_repo.py`) checks:\n- All required files exist ✅ (no files added/removed)\n- `run_safe_scan.sh` contains the string `\"Refusing to scan non-local target\"` ✅ (preserved)\n\nBoth changes would pass validation.\n\n### Limitation\nI was unable to push these changes due to